Berthold type foundry (Berlin). It is one of the most famous earliest Sans Serifs known as Grotesques. As its name says Akzidenz-Grotesk is ideal for jobbing printing, tables, headlines and newsletters. Also the face was frequently used as a body type especially in the middle of the 20th century by a Swiss design movement. Cyrillic version was developed for ParaType in 2002 by Tagir Safayev.
